</tr>
<tr>
<td>Specialty</td>
<td>"bridal hair," "hair extensions," "silk press," "color correction"</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Each of these services deserves its own page on your website. We cover that in Chapter 4.</p>
<h3>Location Keywords</h3>
<p>Salon SEO is local. Clients search with geographic intent.</p>
<p>Combine your service keywords with your city, neighborhood, or zip code. "Balayage Brooklyn" is a different keyword than "balayage Manhattan." Both deserve separate pages if you serve both areas.</p>
<p>Use <a href="/blog/keyword-research-for-blog-posts/">keyword research</a> tools like Google Keyword Planner or <a href="/best/best-free-seo-tools/">free SEO tools</a> to find exact search volumes. Focus on keywords with clear booking intent.</p>
<h3>High-Intent Modifiers</h3>
<p>The most profitable keywords include modifiers that signal a client is ready to book.</p>
